      • createQueryFromExistingMetadata

        public SearchQuery createQueryFromExistingMetadata(IMediaFile res,
                                                   Hints hints)
        creates a query using the sagetv resource. This does not do any file parsing, it simply reads the current state of information in the object and builds a query. This is useful for recorded tv and recored movies that do no require filename scraping.
        Parameters:
        res -

      • createSageFriendlyQuery

        public SearchQuery createSageFriendlyQuery(IMediaFile res,
                                           Hints hints)
        Most resources are Sage Resources, so this attempts to first create a query using the existing Sage Resource to fill in the title, year, episode title, etc.

        If the resource is a recording, airing, or already has a MediaType, then it will simply use the existing metadata from the object as the query. Otherwise it will do a scraped query.

        Parameters:
        res -
